# Bump + restart local (full workflow)

When the user asks to **bump** (version/release) **and restart local**, or clearly means the same (e.g. “ship it”, “release bump”, “bump and restart”), do **all** of the following unless they explicitly opt out of one step:

1. **Bump** — Update repo `VERSION` and move `CHANGELOG.md` `[Unreleased]` into a dated `[X.Y.Z]` section (per `CHANGELOG.md` “Releasing”).
2. **Commit** — `git add` the release-related changes (typically `VERSION`, `CHANGELOG.md`, and any code/docs in that release), write a clear message (e.g. `chore: release vX.Y.Z — …`).
3. **Push** — `git push` to `origin` for the **current branch**. **Do not skip push** unless the user says not to or auth/network fails—report errors clearly.
   - If **`master` (or default branch) is protected** (push rejected, “pull request” required): put the release commit on a branch **`chore/release-vX.Y.Z`**, reset local default branch to match **`origin`**, push **`chore/release-vX.Y.Z`**, and give the **GitHub “Open a pull request”** URL. The workflow still counts as “pushed” once the branch is on `origin`.
4. **Restart local** — Restart the dev server (Windows: `scripts/dev-start.ps1` from repo root, or equivalent `uvicorn` with reload). Note **8766** = dev source vs **8765** = installed service.

**Tagging:** If the project’s release process uses `v*` tags (see `CHANGELOG.md` / CI), remind the user to tag and push tags after the commit, or run `git tag vX.Y.Z && git push origin vX.Y.Z` when they want the installer workflow.

Do **not** treat “bump and restart local” as complete without **push** (after a successful commit).

## When done — tell the user (every time)

After the steps above, **briefly confirm** in your reply:

1. **Version** — `VERSION` is now **vX.Y.Z** and `CHANGELOG.md` is updated.
2. **GitHub** — Commit is **pushed** to `origin` (branch name + PR link if `master` is protected).
3. **Local** — The repo **`VERSION`** file matches the release; **restart** the dev server so the sidebar shows **vX.Y.Z** and migrations run **(dev: `http://127.0.0.1:8766`** unless they use port **8765** for the installed service).
4. **Optional** — Remind them to **merge PR** and **`git tag vX.Y.Z && git push origin vX.Y.Z`** if they use tagged releases / CI.

Do **not** end the task without this **short recap** so they know what to do next on GitHub and locally.

## Full end-to-end (“new version on GitHub + local dev ready”)

When the user wants the **whole workflow** so they can **download the installer** and **test from source**:

1. **Release branch** — Commit + push `chore/release-vX.Y.Z` as usual.
2. **Tag** — `git tag -a vX.Y.Z -m "Release vX.Y.Z"` and `git push origin vX.Y.Z` (triggers **Build installer** on Actions).
3. **Merge to `master`** — If **`master` is protected**, open/merge the PR on GitHub (or confirm **Merge pull request** is done). **Do not assume** `git push origin master` works from the agent shell.
4. **Local sync** — `git fetch origin && git checkout master && git pull origin master` so **`HEAD` matches `origin/master`** and **`VERSION`** matches the release.
5. **Installer** — After Actions finishes, **`GrabbySetup.exe`** is on the **Release** or **workflow Artifacts**. Point them to **`https://github.com/<owner>/<repo>/releases`** (or `/releases/tag/vX.Y.Z`).
6. **Dev server** — Run **`scripts/dev-start.ps1`** (default **8766**). If the port is stuck, **`Stop-Process`** on the owning PID, or use **`-PreferredPort 8767`**.

**Run these git/terminal steps for the user** when they ask for the full workflow—don’t only describe them.
